    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl> <ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/> <citedRange>XV.67</citedRange></bibl> and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#antiTacc"/>, <citedRange>VII.14</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>124</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>097850</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>107</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63360"><name nymRef="#Βακαλ"><supplied reason="lost">Βακ</supplied>αλ</name> 
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ενης"><gap reason="lost" atLeast="3" atMost="5" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><unclear>έ</unclear>νευς</seg></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω"><supplied reason="lost">ἱαριτ</supplied>εύων</w></rs>.
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                 <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Bakal fils de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>énès <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied>, pendant sa prêtrise.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Bakal son of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>enes <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> while being priest.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Bakal figlio di <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>enes <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> quando era sacerdote.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The stone was published by Pugliese in <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>124</citedRange></bibl> from a drawing in Oliverio's papers and has never been seen
                    by anyone else.</p>
                <p>The father's name might be a compound in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-γένης</foreign>, in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-μένης</foreign> or in
                    <foreign xml:lang="grc">-σθένης</foreign>. <foreign xml:lang="grc">Βακαλ</foreign> is a name typical of Cyrenaica and rather rare, 
                    but no example is known in relation with the possible forms mentioned above.</p>
             <p><bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> offers about this inscription wholly hypothetical dating and prosopographical inferences, which we cannot endorse.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
